Chinese man arrested for smuggling powdered human flesh capsules in S Korea
2013-05-28 06:46:36 GMT
By Zhang Yujie, Sina EnglishA Chinese man was arrested by police for smuggling capsules containing powdered human flesh to South Korea, South Korea’s Chosun Ilbo reported on Monday.The man, an ethnic Korean named Kim, has smuggled the so-called "cure-alls" 41 times from China to South Korea since 2004, according to the police.Customs Office seized 120 capsules when the man tried to cross the border on April 8 earlier this year. He claimed those pills as “stomachache medicines”.Human DNA has been detected in those capsules by scientists in South Korea's Institute of Scientific Investigation before police arrested the man. 
